# Release Notes

## Version 1.0.0

### Overview

This release implements comprehensive CLI Tool Standards ADR compliance for {{ project_name }}, providing a production-ready TypeScript CLI boilerplate with 35 standards across 9 development phases.

### Major Features

#### Core Standards
- **Enhanced Color Control**: Automatic color detection with chalk and supports-color
- **Standard Exit Codes**: Consistent exit codes (0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 130)
- **Configuration File Initialization**: Auto-initialization of config files

#### Configuration & Logging
- **Enhanced Logging Modes**: Quiet, normal, verbose, debug, and JSON modes
- **Configuration Precedence Chain**: 6-level precedence (CLI args > env vars > local > user > system > defaults)
- **Structured Logging**: Auto-detection of JSON/text format

#### Installation & Documentation
- **Install/Uninstall Flags**: Easy CLI installation and cleanup
- **Shell Completion Scripts**: Bash, zsh, and fish completions
- **Man Pages**: Automatic man page generation

#### User Experience
- **Dry-Run Mode**: Preview changes without execution
- **Confirmation Prompts**: Interactive prompts for destructive operations
- **Progress Indicators**: Progress bars for long-running operations
- **Pager Integration**: Automatic paging for long output
- **Terminal Size Awareness**: Responsive output based on terminal dimensions

#### Advanced Features
- **TUI Mode**: Interactive Terminal User Interface
- **Daemon Process Support**: Background job management
- **File Reference Formatting**: Clickable file references in output
- **URL Formatting**: OSC 8 clickable URLs in supported terminals

#### Configuration & Security
- **Configuration Validation**: Schema-based config validation
- **Config Auto-Migration**: Automatic version migration
- **Credential/Secret Handling**: Secret redaction from logs
- **Signal-Based Config Reload**: SIGHUP for config reload without restart

#### Cross-Platform & Resources
- **Cross-Platform Path Handling**: Path normalization for Windows, Linux, macOS
- **Resource Limits**: Memory and CPU usage limits
- **Collection vs Processing Separation**: Offline data analysis capability

#### Quality & Maintenance
- **Error Message Formatting**: Structured error messages with suggestions
- **Health Checks for Containers**: Health endpoints for container orchestration
- **Privacy Mode**: Data redaction for anonymous usage
- **Audit Logging**: Tamper-evident audit logging
- **Legacy Deprecation Policy**: 6-month minimum deprecation period

#### Organization & Quality
- **Subcommand Organization**: Hierarchical command structure (completion, man, daemon, health, audit, deprecation)
- **Comprehensive Test Coverage**: >80% code coverage with 26 test files
- **Testing Strategy**: Documented testing approach with CI integration

